<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-39-1256 </DOCNO><TEXT>Serious allegations of weld X-ray forging during construction of one ofBritain's nuclear power stations have been refuted by the Nuclear InstallationsInspectorate following a five month long investigation into the conductof a sub-contract welding company working in the seventies. But the investigationhas thrust sharply into focus the ease with which unscrupulous staffcould cover up a defective weld by X-ray substitution.</TEXT></DOC>